OL,7,FHe has lived here on and off for a
OL,8,Fdecade, during a long stint as a
OL,9,Fstudent. Next month he will graduate
OL,10,Ffrom Columbia University, where pro-
OL,11,FPalestinian protests paralysed parts
OL,12,Fof the campus last year.
OL,14,FAlthough he stood back from these
OL,15,Fnoisy encampments, he was still a
OL,16,Fleading voice among students on the
OL,17,Fissue of Gaza. His background as a
OL,18,Fthird-generation refugee from the West
OL,19,FBank informs his opinions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
